{
  "stem": "20609.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "He-- he had a big bottle of beer and he took out the biggest sandwich I ever saw in my life, one of those big sandwiches, and he started eating and drinking the beer and the-- and the thing is I was ready to kill this guy for that sandwich.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I would have-- I mean, well, I ate whatever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I could-- I could-- every bite.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "I think the worst part about it was the food in that camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "You were really were on a starvation diet and-- and we worked very hard.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[DRINKS] But one of the advantages were A, you got outside the camp, you got away from the smell; and many times, you chopped wood where there was, like, fields with spinach so you grabbed some spinach, put in your-- in your pants and bring it in, you know.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "So-- and-- and some of the time, the guards didn't want to look.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "We didn't always have SSS.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "We had meat mainly Czechoslovakian gendarmes, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "They used to call them Chetniks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And those were-- they worked for the Germans, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "These were Czechoslovakians and some of them were good and some them were a piece of garbage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "So we were in a position to pull in a little bit and you could trade us up for-- for an extra piece of bread or something like that, you know.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And so it started-- it started and I see already had the light and I know what's going on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And I have a dish, I know how I can grab some stuff in and so forth.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now, but it's still hard work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So you see, Theresienstadt was a very unique camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
